{
  "stem": "3360.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And is-- it's a whole different thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But academically, it's on an equal with everything else.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So those most observant Jewish-- those children from more observing Jewish homes, they would have been enrolled in that other-- in the Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was not.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was in a public school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a display of unbelievable-- it was an unbelievable vision to walk through that whole street when those flags were out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And what it reminded me of, like a premonition or whatever that was, because I knew what Nazism meant for us Jews, even though we weren't terribly observing Jews.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It reminded me of blood all over, up and down the street.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it, it was a horrible sight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, 19-- we-- yes, we moved there when I was six years old.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was, it was out there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You, you just knew about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you knew about all the other parties.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Germany was-- unfortunately, that was one of the other big problems, that there were too many political parties in Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Nazis, the National Socialists, had become one of the major parties.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[COUGHING] It was just something that you knew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We-- there was no television.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't even have a radio, but you knew it because your parents talked about it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were-- I must say, that looking back, I would think that we were quite sophisticated in knowing what was going on and being aware of those things.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, of course, the danger that Nazism posed to us as Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my mother was very worried that, you know, that they would get into-- that they would be elected.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as it turned out to be, historically, they never actually had a majority of votes of the German people, the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
